---
const advantages = [
  {
    emoji: "🎖",
    title: "Veteran-owned & accountable",
    sub: "SDVOSB, SAM registered — a real name behind the work",
  },
  {
    emoji: "🚫",
    title: "No hype, no filler",
    sub: "Straight answers and honest scope, even when it costs us the upsell",
  },
  {
    emoji: "🛠",
    title: "One operator, end to end",
    sub: "The person who scopes it is the person who builds and ships it",
  },
  {
    emoji: "🔎",
    title: "Work you can verify",
    sub: "Shipped apps, a live intel feed, and handoffs you can actually check",
  },
];
---
<section class="advantage advantage-right" id="why-bulwark">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="advantage-grid">
      <div class="advantage-visual reveal order-first">
        <p class="advantage-eyebrow">What you get</p>
        <div class="chip-row">
          {
            advantages.map((a) => (
              <div class="chip-tile">
                <span class="chip-emoji">{a.emoji}</span>
                <div>
                  <div class="chip-title">{a.title}</div>
                  <div class="chip-sub">{a.sub}</div>
                </div>
              </div>
            ))
          }
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="reveal">
        <span class="section-label">Why Bulwark Black</span>
        <h2 class="section-title advantage-title-left">
          A small shop is the feature,<br />not the compromise.
        </h2>
        <p class="advantage-body">
          Most technical work fails on communication, not code. Briefs get lost
          between the salesperson, the account manager, and whoever actually
          builds the thing. Here, that whole chain is one veteran-owned team, so
          nothing gets lost in translation and there is always someone
          accountable to call.
        </p>
        <p class="advantage-body">
          We say no when a project is not a fit, tell you when the simple option
          is the right one, and hand off documented work you can maintain
          without us. The daily threat-intelligence feed is the proof of work:
          public, current, and free to read.
        </p>
        <p class="advantage-body">
          You are not hiring a logo or a call center. You are hiring the person
          who ships it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
